  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (b3fe652 2022-04-18T00:12:45.381840+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSee this test: \r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n    function testSetFeeTo() public {\r\n        assertEq(engine.feeTo(), FEE_TO);\r\n        VM.expectRevert();\r\n        engine.setFeeTo(ALICE);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nFrom here:\r\nhttps://github.com/Alcibiades-Capital/valorem-options-contracts/blob/tabula_rasa/src/test/OptionSettlement.t.sol#L146\r\n\r\nProduces the failure output:\r\n```\r\n[11837] OptionSettlementTest::testSetFeeTo()\r\n    ├─ [2383] OptionSettlementEngine::feeTo() [staticcall]\r\n    │   └─ ← 0x36273803306a3c22bc848f8db761e974697ece0d\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::expectRevert()\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [736] OptionSettlementEngine::setFeeTo(0x000000000000000000000000000000000000000a)\r\n    │   └─ ← \"AccessControlViolation(0xb4c79dab8f259c7aee6e5b2aa729821864227e84, 0x36273803306a3c22bc848f8db761e974697ece0d)\"\r\n    └─ ← \"AccessControlViolation(0xb4c79dab8f259c7aee6e5b2aa729821864227e84, 0x36273803306a3c22bc848f8db761e974697ece0d)\"\r\n```\r\n    \r\nWhen the revert should be expected. The same happens when using the `bytes4` selector.",
